A model described in the PRISM language consist of a set of modules that can interact with each other. The state of each module is being represented by the value of a set of finite-ranging variables. The global state of the whole model is determined by the local state of all modules. The behavior of each module is described by a set of commands of the form:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
